\f1\b Common
\f0\b0 \
\
a. Work Type: This property tells to the script how to run. As of now, we are using only \'93Reflect\'94 option. Other values are saved for further implementations. So you have to select \'93Reflect\'94 for your reflective surfaces.\
\
b. Up Vector: This property defines the up vector of the object which will reflect the scene. Most of the time object\'92s up vector is \'93Green Y\'94 and you do not have to change that. But if object has a different up vector (coming with a different value via 3d program like 3ds max) you can set it here.\
\
c. Intensity: As the name describes it just changes the reflection intensity. 1 (one) is full reflective (full mirror), and it blends with the real texture of the object as it goes down to 0 (zero).\
\
d. Disable G Buffer: Disables the GI buffers. If you want to make perfect mirrors you can check this. So it does not add lightning artifacts to reflection.\
\
e. Disable R Probes: Disables the reflection probes. In deferred rendering path, reflection probes may be merged with the reflection and cause unwanted artifacts. You can disable them here, so reflection will appear more real.\
\
f. Run For Every Xth Frame: It just draws the reflection for the Xth frame of the app. So script draws the reflection for every Xth frame (uses the last capture for other ones). 1 (one) is the default and it is realtime. If you increase the value, you may gain fps but reflection loses the reality.\
\
g. Camera LOD Level: LOD level of the camera. Yuu can change the camera LOD level to draw the scene. So you may gain fps by drawing smaller LODs if you have.\
\
h. Texture LOD Level: Lod level of the reflection texture. It may be used for blurred reflections (you can mix it with Final Texture option and increase the blur).\
\
