\cf5 Camera
\f0\b0 \
\
a. HDR: Enables HDR for reflection (HDR must be enabled on graphic settings). And it also activates the \'93Post Process Stack\'94 effects. So if you turn it on, post effects automatically will be added to reflection.\
\
b. MSAA: Enables MSAA for reflection  (works on Forward rendering only, it must be enabled on graphic settings). On deferred rendering if a post anti aliasing is added, it automatically will be applied if HDR is on.\
\
c. Disable Pixel Lights: Disables the pixel lights on render. It may increase the fps but you may lose the reality of the reflection.\
\
d. Shadows: If true, it enables the shadow distance setting on the reflection.\
d.1 Shadow Distance: Works only if \'93Shadows\'94 is true. You can set the distance of the shadow pass for reflection. So if you put \'930\'94 there reflection will not render any shadow and you may gain speed especially on mobile. Or you can set the distance according to camera and render the shadows of the nearby objects only.\
\
e. Cull: If true, enables a cull distance for the camera.\
e.1. Cull Distance: Works only if \'93Cull\'94 is true. You can set the spherical draw distance for the reflection camera. SO you render only the objects which are close to the camera (or your plane-surface for the mirror). SO you may gain very much speed for just not drawing the whole screen but only in the culling distance objects!\
\
f. Texture Size: It is the quality of the reflection. 2048 gives the best results but of course it will decrease the fps. You may select the power of two values like 256, 512, 1024, 2048 etc. Try and find the best looking value according to your scene.\
\
g. Use Camera Clip Plane: (Not used in this version)\
\
h. Clip Plane Offset: It just moves the reflection forward or backward if you see undesired artifacts. The script calculates the perfect offset according to your object so you do not have to adjust it most of the time.\
\
i. Reflect Layers: You can reflect the selected layers according to your needs. For example if there are expensive objects on your scene to draw, you can put them on a different layer and exclude that layer here. So script will not draw them and you will gain performance.\
\

\f1\b Depth:
\f0\b0 \
\
a. Enable Depth: Enables the depth pass.\
\
b. Depth Cutoff: Changes the depth\'92s depth :) So you can change the how far of the depth should be visible.\
\
c. Depth Blur: Depth blur size according to distance. Shader just blurs the far away pixels (depth) according to this value. May require big values according to scene.\

\f1\b \
Effected Objects and Materials:
\f0\b0 \
\
a. Shades: This is an array which holds the reflective objects and materials in it.\
\
First Slot: Object to Shade: You have put your gameObject here which will reflect the scene (like a plane).\
\
Second Slot: Material to Change: It will hold the material of the previous slot\'92s object.\
\
So you can use as many as objects and materials to shade with current reflection. \'93Camera Shade\'94 script draws the reflection and uses it on every \'93Shade\'94 array. This helps you to use current reflection on several objects. For example you can draw a bathroom which holds a lot of separate mirrors in it.\

\f1\b \
IMPORTANT: 
\f0\b0 The shade objects must be on same plane and direction (like mirrors on same wall).\
\

\f1\b Shader to Run on Final Texture: 
\f0\b0 This option runs a second shader on reflection. So we can get blurred etc. reflections easily.\
\
a. Enable Final Shader: Set to true to enable extra shader pass!\
\
b. Final Shader: Shader to run on reflection texture (like \'93BlursLod\'94)\
\
c. Enable AR Mode: If you want to blur the AR reflection (full transparency), check this to blur the texture. Without this texture may blurred with random black pixels!\
\
d. Iterations: This shader will run X times on reflection. So we can generate more beautiful effects.\
\
e. Neighbor Pixels: Every pixel will be calculated according to Xth neighbor pixel. So some shaders can handle the effects more beautiful.\
\
f. Block Size: Will be used on next releases. Does not work on this release.\

\f1\b \
Refraction
\f0\b0 \
\
a. Refraction Texture: If you want to refract the reflection you may attach a bump map here.\
\
b. Refraction: It is the value of the refraction. 0 (zero) is no refraction, it refracts the reflection as it goes upper values.\

\f1\b \
Waves
\f0\b0 \
\
a. Enable Waves: Set to true to enable waves on reflection.\
\
b. Wave Noise Texture: Set a bump map to create waves. Different maps will create different waves.\
\
c. Wave Size: Changes the wave size. Bigger values creates bigger waves.\
\
d. Wave Distortion: Changes the distortion of the reflection according to the noise texture. Big values may distort the reflection very much. So try to use small values.\
\
e. Wave Speed: Changes the speed of the waves.\

\f1\b \
Ripples
\f0\b0 \
\
a. Enable Ripples: Set to true to enable ripples.\
\
b. Ripple Texture: Ripple normal-map texture that carries ripple normals.\
\
c. Ripple Size: Changes the size of the ripples. Bigger values makes the ripples smaller.\
\
d. Ripple Refraction: Refracts the texture on ripple. Uses the normals of the texture. Bigger values makes more refracted texture (reflection).\
\
e. Ripple Density: Changes the density of the ripples. Bigger values makes more visible ripples.\
\
f. Ripple Speed: Changes the speed of the ripples. So you can simulate the fast rains, storms etc.\

\f1\b \
Masking
\f0\b0 \
\
a. Enable Mask: Set to true if you want masking.\
\
b. Mask Texture: The masking texture which carries alpha information to apply on reflection.\
\
c. Mask Tiling: Because all textures uses main materials tiling you may want to set different uv\'92s for mask tile. So you can play with this values to get your correct masking (looking).\
\
d. Mask Cutoff: Cutoff value for mask texture.\
\
e. Mask Edge Darkness: It is a value to give a darker look in the corners of the mask. The default value is 1 (one) which does not give any darkness. If you increase the value you have to get nice darker corner around the mask (just to give a simple wet looking corners).\
\
